<head>
<title>Medical Innovation Project -- PFF</title>
</head>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/pff/notebook.gif" LINK="#8C1717" VLINK="#545454" ALINK="#FF0000"> <ul><blockquote><a href="/pff"><img src="/pff/pffdoc.gif" align="right" border="0"></a>

<h1><center>Medical Innovation Project</center></h1>
<p>
Civilization is poised to make major strides in medicine and health. These
advances have the potential to dramatically increase both life spans and quality
of life, while at the same time reducing the cost of health care. Yet all of this
progress and our ability to realize fully the benefits of these advances is
threatened by an outmoded regulatory framework.<p> 

The Foundation's Medical Innovation Project seeks to replace the current process
by which new drugs and medical devices are brought to market in the United
States. Under the leadership of Dr. Louis Sullivan, former Secretary of Health
and Human Services, the Medical Innovation Project is well advanced in its
efforts to develop a much more privately focused system to make sure that
beneficial drugs and medical devices are brought to the market while still
ensuring their safety and effectiveness. <p>

The MIP is currently designing, in complete and comprehensive form, ready for
implementation, a new process by which new drugs and other medical technologies
are tested and made available to consumers for the early part of the 21st
century. A major thrust of the project is to explore avenues for dramatically
increasing the role of the private sector in the testing and certification
process and, accordingly, shifting the government's role to one of oversight of
the process rather than operations per se. <p>

<i>For more information contact: <a href="mailto:LWright@pff.org">LWright@pff.org</a>.</i><p>
<UL>
<li><A HREF="/pff/mip_advisory.html">Medical Innovation Project Advisory Committee</A>
<li><A HREF="/pff/project/tl-1019.html">End the FDA Monopoly</a> by Thomas M. Lenard
<img alt="New" img align="middle" src="/townhall/new.gif">
<li><a href="/pff/project/rubin.html">Direct-to-Consumer Promotion</a> by Paul H. Rubin
<img alt="New" img align="middle" src="/townhall/new.gif">
<li><a href="new-approach-med.html">The Future of Medical Innovation: A New Approach For Bringing Medical Products to Market</a>
<li><a href="replace-fda.html">Plan to Replace and Improve FDA Approval Process Unveiled</a>
<li><a href="/pff/project/tl-test.html">Congressional Testimony on Approval Procedure for Medical Devices</a>  
<LI><a href="/pff/project/tl-1004.html">End the FDA Approval Monopoly</a> by Thomas M. Lenard
</ul>
<p>

<center>



</center>

<p>
</blockquote></ul><p><br><center><a href="/pff/footer.map"><img src="/pff/footer.gif" border="0" ISMAP></a></center></BODY>
