<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<center>




<h2>Town Hall Guest Columnist<p>
John A. Baden</h2>


</center>


<h5><a href="/townhall/columnists/i-baden.html.cgi">[Graphics On]</a></h5>
<hr size="3" width="60%">








<p>





<a href="/townhall/columnists/baden.html"><b>Biography</b></a>
<ul>

        <LI><A HREF="Primer2.ST1996.html">Clinton's 'Green Decrees':  Easy Answers Postpone Reform</A> - 10/16/96


<LI><A HREF="Primer1.ST1996.html">Avoid Political Extinction with A New Shade of Green</A> - 10/2/96


<LI><A HREF="GreenThumbs.ST1996.html">Using Green Thumbs to Hitch an Internet Ride</A> - 9/18/96


<LI><A HREF="Entrep.ST1996.html">Entrepreneurs Harmonize Economies with Ecology</A> - 9/4/96





<li>August 21, 1996 <a href="/free/ST96/Salmon.ST1996.html">Conquest of the Columbia Carried Tremendous Costs</a>
<li>August 7, 1996 <a href="/free/ST96/Parasite.ST1996.html">Finding Defenses Against Parasitic Bureaucracies</a>
<li>July 19, 1996 <a href="/free/ST96/Parks.ST1996.html">Park Lovers Can Save National Parks</a>
<li>June 28, 1996 <a href="/free/ST96/FJ96.ST1996.html">Effective Environmentalism Uses a New Shade of Green</a>
<li>June 24, 1996 <a href="/free/pubs/Liberty.OSF.html">Flying Blind or Running Scared?</a>
<li>June 24, 1996 <a href="/free/pubs/TAE.OSF.html">Al Gore's Newest Horror Story</a>
<li>June 24, 1996 <a href="/free/pubs/WSJ.USFS.html">Resource Politics Miss The Forest For the Trees</a>
<li>June 3, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/baden/bade052996.html">The Predictable Perversities of Bureaucratic Behavior</a>
<li>May 24, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/baden/bade051596.html">Fostering A New West That Respects Old Values</a>
<p><a href="/free/ST96/FREE.ST1996.html">Archive</a><p>
</ul>

